                    { "text": "Jenkins X", "zone": "tools" },
                    { "text": "Declarative configuration", "zone": "practices" },
                    { "text": "Single source of truth (Git)", "zone": "practices" }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "title": "Lesson 4: Infrastructure as Code (IaC)",
            "navTitle": "Infrastructure as Code",
            "cards": [
                {
                    "title": "What is IaC?",
                    "content": [
                        { "type": "concept", "title": "Infrastructure as Code", "value": "Describes infrastructure using declarative definition files. Tools apply these definitions to create or update resources." },
                        { "type": "highlight", "value": "IaC = Declarative infrastructure configuration in code" }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "title": "Benefits of IaC",
                    "content": [
                        { "type": "grid", "columns": 2, "items": [
                            { "icon": "⚡", "title": "Faster Setup", "text": "Provision infrastructure in minutes" },
                            { "icon": "🔄", "title": "Reproducible", "text": "Identical environments every time" },
                            { "icon": "📖", "title": "Human-Readable", "text": "Configuration in plain text" },
                            { "icon": "📦", "title": "Version Control", "text": "Stored in Git with history" },
                            { "icon": "🎯", "title": "No Drift", "text": "Live state matches definitions" },
                            { "icon": "🤖", "title": "Automated", "text": "Apply changes with commands" }
                        ]}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "title": "Terraform Example",
                    "content": [
                        { "type": "text", "value": "This Terraform file provisions a VM in AWS:" },
                        { "type": "code", "language": "hcl", "value": "terraform {\n  required_providers {\n    aws = {\n      source  = \"hashicorp/aws\"\n      version = \"~> 4.16\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nprovider \"aws\" {\n  region = \"eu-central-1\"\n}\n\nresource \"aws_instance\" \"kcna_demo_vm\" {\n  ami           = \"ami-051835d754b74795c\"\n  instance_type = \"t3.medium\"\n\n  tags = {\n    Name = \"KCNAExampleInstance\"\n  }\n}" },
                        { "type": "keypoint", "badge": "Scope", "value": "IaC can manage VMs, load balancers, storage, firewall rules, and more." }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "title": "IaC and Kubernetes",
                    "content": [
                        { "type": "keypoint", "badge": "Natural Fit", "value": "Kubernetes itself uses declarative configuration, making it a natural fit for IaC and GitOps." },
                        { "type": "list", "items": [
                            "Kubernetes manifests are IaC definitions",
                            "Helm charts package IaC for reuse",
                            "Kustomize provides IaC customization",
                            "GitOps tools sync K8s manifests to clusters"
                        ]}
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "lab": {
                "title": "IaC Benefits",
                "type": "dragdrop",
